ID   CheR_CheB_C
DE   Chemotaxis protein methyltransferase/methylesterase C-terminal region
AU   Bateman A;0000-0002-6982-4660
SE   TED:A0LD36_TED01
GA   27.00 27.00;
TC   27.70 28.00;
NC   26.60 26.70;
BM   hmmbuild  -o /dev/null HMM SEED
SM   hmmsearch --cpu 8 -E 1000 -Z 90746521 HMM pfamseq
TP   Family
CC   This entry represents a C-terminal region (approximately 565-646
CC   residues) found in two-component system chemotaxis proteins with
CC   methyltransferase (CheR) and methylesterase (CheB) activity. These
CC   proteins contain CheB_methylest, CheR_N, CheR and PAS domains and are
CC   involved in bacterial chemotaxis signalling. The family is found in
CC   Thermodesulfobacteriota (Desulfovibrionia, Desulfobacteria,
CC   Desulfuromonadia, Desulfovibrionales, Desulfobacterales,
CC   Geobacterales), Pseudomonadota (Gammaproteobacteria), Bacillota
CC   (Bacilli, Bacillales, Clostridia) and Bacteroidota (Cytophagia,
CC   Cytophagales).
